Key Match Events: Javier Assad yielded two runs (one earned) and three hits, struck out five and walked three in 5⅔ innings.
Pete Crow-Armstrong made a notable defensive play by catching a fly ball and throwing to first baseman Michael Busch to catch Alex Verdugo off the base, although the call was overturned.
Javier Assad struck out Juan Soto with a 93.3 mph sinker to end the fifth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Craig Counsell commented on Javier Assad's performance, stating 'He pitched very well. He did his job.'
